documentation.text:
@title Lottery
 @dev A simple decentralized lottery smart contract.
@dev Constructor initializes the contract with the contract owner and sets the initial lottery ID.

@dev Get the balance of the contract in ether.
 @return The balance of the contract.

@dev Get the list of players who entered the current lottery.
 @return An array of addresses representing the players.
@dev Enter the lottery by sending a minimum value of 0.01 ether.

@dev Generate a pseudo-random number based on the owner's address and current timestamp.
 @return A pseudo-random number.

@dev Pick a winner from the list of players and transfer the contract's balance to them.
 Only the contract owner can call this function.

documentation.text: @dev Modifier to ensure that only the contract owner can call certain functions.

devdoc.details: A simple decentralized lottery smart contract.

constructor.details: Constructor initializes the contract with the contract owner and sets the initial lottery ID.

enter().details: Enter the lottery by sending a minimum value of 0.01 ether.

getBalance().details: Get the balance of the contract in ether.

getPlayers().details: Get the list of players who entered the current lottery.

returns._0: An array of addresses representing the players.

getRandomNumber().details: Generate a pseudo-random number based on the owner's address and current timestamp.

getWinnerByLottery(uint256).details: Get the winner's address for a specific lottery ID.

returns._0: The winner's address for the given lottery.

pickWinner().details: Pick a winner from the list of players and transfer the contract's balance to them. Only the contract owner can call this function.
